cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a new quantization method for gate parameters in the LSTM neural network model, which is a common model used in natural language processing tasks such as Named Entity Recognition. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as backpropagation and optimization, which are covered in cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses experiments to validate the proposed method, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper focuses on the LSTM model, which is a type of recurrent neural network, and therefore could also be classified under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
